   <text>
      <body>
         <div>
            <head>13.09.1880 Montag</head>
            <p>
               <placeName type="write" key="49050">London</placeName> Monday 13 September 1880</p>
            <p>Today <persName key="15536">Uncle Tom</persName> took me to see his yacht being built
               at <orgName key="66928">Forrestt the boatbuilders</orgName>. Little of it is yet
               done only just the mere Carcasse and as far as I can judge by the beams this is its
               plan. A forecastle room for the sailor 6 feet, a bedroom for passengers, 6 feet, an
               engine room 20 feet, a back room for passengers 7 1/2 feet, a pantry and a W. C.
               running into the engine room. It is all mahogany and is to have two masts and one
               chimney. <persName key="15536">Uncle Tom</persName> and the boatbuilder fought a good
               deal about it and <persName key="15536">Uncle Tom</persName> and <persName key="2906">Harry Lynch</persName> his son are going to see it tomorrow again</p>
            <p>Harry<space/>H de Kessler</p>
         </div>
